  "instructions": [
    "heat the olive oil in a large tagine or Dutch oven over medium heat.",
    "add the onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "add the garlic and cook for 1 minute more.",
    "add the chicken thighs and cook until browned on all sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "add the doenjang, chicken broth, almonds, flour, water, flaky sea salt, black pepper, and red pepper flakes to the pot.",
    "bring the mixture to a simmer and cook, covered, until the chicken is cooked through and the sauce has thickened, about 20 minutes.",
    "flambé the sauce with a small amount of cognac or rum, if desired.",
    "serve the tagine hot, garnished with fresh parsley.",
    "serve over couscous or rice, if desired."
  ],
